        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 8:23PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 822 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Lincoln, or 27 miles northeast of Drummond, moving east
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lincoln.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
